sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1679011
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a device containing a promoter(BBa_J23106),a RBS(BBa_K115002) and a RFP coding sequence(BBa_E1010) on the pSB1C3 ,which can be easily transformed into E.coli.Then the E.coli would produce RFP when the temperature rises above 37??C.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Cun Wei
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We use a special RBS(BBa_K115002) to make the device temperature-sensitive.When the temperature is below 37??C,the secondary structure of the RBS after transform would be folded.Thus the ribosome can't translated RFP.However,when the temperature rises above 42??C,the secondary structure of the RBS after transform would be unfolded and produce RFP.
